cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper focuses on developing a self-supervised learning framework for 3D medical images using a novel proxy task. This involves training 3D neural networks to learn translational and rotational invariant features from raw 3D data. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning networks, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper proposes a pre-training strategy that could be related to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper focuses on medical imaging, which could also place it in the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia).
